1
00:00:02,040 --> 00:00:03,940
I was waiting for you.

2
00:00:05,800 --> 00:00:08,140
It's dangerous for a woman to be alone.

3
00:00:08,140 --> 00:00:10,380
I've seen this in a book before.

4
00:00:10,380 --> 00:00:14,640
That the moment doesn't start with difficult words.

5
00:00:15,820 --> 00:00:17,760
Please wear these.

6
00:00:17,760 --> 00:00:19,760
Your legs hurt, don't they?

7
00:00:19,760 --> 00:00:25,640
Rather, it can start, not with some grandiose modifiers, but with just simple words.

8
00:00:30,160 --> 00:00:31,780
Wow!

9
00:01:16,000 --> 00:01:20,860
That moment  it seems someone is protecting me.

10
00:01:25,640 --> 00:01:30,920
Is there a sound in love too?

11
00:01:34,000 --> 00:01:36,120
That's a disease.

12
00:01:36,120 --> 00:01:40,340
When your heartbeat is irregular, you have to consider  arrhythmia or diabetes.
Episode 3

13
00:01:41,200 --> 00:01:43,060
Stop spoiling it!

14
00:01:43,060 --> 00:01:48,020
Do you know how much a woman's heart flutters when someone protects them?

15
00:01:48,020 --> 00:01:49,860
So what's your point?

16
00:01:49,860 --> 00:01:52,260
I don't know either.

17
00:01:52,260 --> 00:01:56,400
There's that moment, you know, when there are a lot of high heels in a store,

18
00:01:56,400 --> 00:01:59,450
but there's one that just catches my eye right away!

19
00:01:59,950 --> 00:02:03,510
My heart beats like crazy when that happens.

20
00:02:03,510 --> 00:02:05,160
I have to buy those heels.

21
00:02:05,160 --> 00:02:08,350
So that friend is a pair of heels that makes your heart flutter?

22
00:02:08,350 --> 00:02:13,270
But would that friend know that you think of him as a pair of shoes?

23
00:02:13,270 --> 00:02:15,790
Shouldn't I not let that chance get away?

24
00:02:15,790 --> 00:02:18,110
Don't go overboard over one umbrella!

25
00:02:18,110 --> 00:02:21,010
When you start a relationship with a younger guy,

26
00:02:21,010 --> 00:02:24,490
right when he says he can't live without you,

27
00:02:24,490 --> 00:02:28,190
you have to barely give him a chance.

28
00:02:31,550 --> 00:02:33,250
You eat it.

29
00:02:33,250 --> 00:02:37,550
No no no. There's so much collagen in chicken feet. It's good for preventing aging.

30
00:02:37,550 --> 00:02:39,350
Really?

31
00:02:41,210 --> 00:02:44,210
It's delicious.

32
00:02:48,490 --> 00:02:51,950
Don't go overboard over one umbrella!

33
00:02:53,710 --> 00:02:58,580
Yeah... It might be that I'm thinking too far ahead.

34
00:03:17,290 --> 00:03:20,790
Fighting today too!
Seong Jae.

35
00:03:32,110 --> 00:03:35,550
How can I not misunderstand when he acts like this?

36
00:03:36,840 --> 00:03:37,980
You've come?

37
00:03:37,980 --> 00:03:39,840
Ah, hot!

38
00:03:41,040 --> 00:03:42,960
Thank you, Seong Jae.

39
00:03:42,960 --> 00:03:46,460
I organized the weekly best sales and put it in the computer.

40
00:03:46,460 --> 00:03:48,560
Ah, really?

41
00:03:51,640 --> 00:03:52,730
Where is it?

42
00:03:52,730 --> 00:03:55,640
Over there.

43
00:04:03,540 --> 00:04:05,280
Here it is.

44
00:04:05,280 --> 00:04:07,400
You're right.

45
00:04:08,040 --> 00:04:09,720
If you don't need anything else...

46
00:04:09,720 --> 00:04:11,200
I don't.

47
00:04:11,200 --> 00:04:15,000
I'm going to see the director.

48
00:04:25,480 --> 00:04:29,020
Oh Ha Na, let's not go overboard. Okay?

49
00:04:31,360 --> 00:04:34,000
I heard you weren't able to meet Gu Yeon Jeong.

50
00:04:34,820 --> 00:04:37,760
Ah, yes. I went to her house, but she wasn't home.

51
00:04:37,760 --> 00:04:40,940
I heard the apparel team leader met her though.

52
00:04:40,940 --> 00:04:43,760
I heard she went all the way to Tokyo to find her.

53
00:04:43,760 --> 00:04:48,290
She got an okay for an appearance in the Fall/Winter Fashion Show.

54
00:04:48,300 --> 00:04:51,900
So what if the design team works hard? The marketing team needs to follow up.

55
00:04:51,920 --> 00:04:53,210
Am I right?

56
00:05:10,630 --> 00:05:14,310
Aigoo, what do I do? My baby. She keeps crying,

57
00:05:14,310 --> 00:05:17,350
"Mother, save me!" This won't do.

58
00:05:17,350 --> 00:05:19,940
Excuse me, please let my  Josephine out!

59
00:05:19,940 --> 00:05:23,560
She's saying, 'I think I'm going to suffocate!'

60
00:05:23,560 --> 00:05:25,380
Can you please quiet that one?

61
00:05:25,380 --> 00:05:27,400
I can't sleep because of the dog barking!

62
00:05:27,400 --> 00:05:29,980
Shut up! You can just cover up your ears and sleep!

63
00:05:29,980 --> 00:05:32,740
Hurry up. My Josephine...

64
00:05:32,740 --> 00:05:35,020
- Hurry!
- The regulations...

65
00:05:35,020 --> 00:05:38,150
Hurry! Hurry!

66
00:05:39,050 --> 00:05:42,420
You're coming out soon, Josephine. Freedom.

67
00:05:42,420 --> 00:05:44,090
Customer.

68
00:05:45,200 --> 00:05:47,660
We have to keep pets in cages.

69
00:05:47,660 --> 00:05:50,410
I think we clearly told you the regulations.

70
00:05:50,410 --> 00:05:52,930
When? Regulations? I don't know about that!

71
00:05:52,930 --> 00:05:56,610
I'm getting off! I'm getting on the next plane with Josephine!

72
00:05:56,610 --> 00:05:58,270
Pilot, come out!

73
00:05:58,270 --> 00:06:01,330
Customer, he's currently piloting the plane.

74
00:06:01,330 --> 00:06:03,350
I'm a VIP customer.

75
00:06:03,350 --> 00:06:06,820
I'm a relative of the vice president's in-laws. Call him right away!

76
00:06:06,820 --> 00:06:10,240
I want to go back! Let me off! I'm getting off!

77
00:06:10,240 --> 00:06:12,740
Customer, please wait a moment.

78
00:06:12,740 --> 00:06:14,590
I'll take care of it.

79
00:06:17,240 --> 00:06:21,380
Oh, my baby.

80
00:07:03,600 --> 00:07:05,160
Thank you.

81
00:07:06,040 --> 00:07:10,820
Sunbae, there are three mysteries in life.

82
00:07:10,820 --> 00:07:13,720
The first one, when will the Tower of Pisa fall down?

83
00:07:13,720 --> 00:07:14,850
And the second,

84
00:07:14,850 --> 00:07:18,080
why do women go together to the bathroom?

85
00:07:18,080 --> 00:07:22,960
Finally the third, how could a picky sunbae like you

86
00:07:22,960 --> 00:07:28,460
become a flight crew member dependent on customer service?

87
00:07:31,120 --> 00:07:33,200
Way to joke around.

88
00:07:34,160 --> 00:07:37,820
Right? I'm sorry.

89
00:07:40,340 --> 00:07:44,280
Are you in your right mind or not? Don't you know taking pets out of their cage is against the regulations?!

90
00:07:44,280 --> 00:07:47,820
The customers were getting very angry since the dog kept barking.

91
00:07:47,820 --> 00:07:50,060
The dog seemed like it needed to be calmed down too.

92
00:07:50,060 --> 00:07:53,020
I was going to take her out for a moment and put her back in.

93
00:07:53,020 --> 00:07:54,960
So, are you now saying you did a good thing?

94
00:07:54,960 --> 00:07:56,000
That's not it.

95
00:07:56,000 --> 00:07:57,320
If you go against the regulations once more,

96
00:07:57,320 --> 00:08:00,140
you'll have to write letter of resignation. Okay?

97
00:08:18,560 --> 00:08:20,300
Are you okay?

98
00:08:21,680 --> 00:08:25,040
Don't be upset since regulations are regulations.

99
00:08:25,040 --> 00:08:29,880
I'm fine. The newest member learns like this.

100
00:08:29,880 --> 00:08:35,680
My mom told me that people scold you out of care for you.

101
00:08:35,680 --> 00:08:39,780
You're optimistic. So optimistic.

102
00:08:42,080 --> 00:08:44,820
That was a compliment just now. Right?

103
00:08:44,820 --> 00:08:47,240
You were complimenting me right now, right?

104
00:08:48,430 --> 00:08:54,210
Manager, how can a celebrity's manager not know when she's returning to Korea?

105
00:08:54,210 --> 00:08:59,950
You're certain this time, right? Last time, our team leader, who was waiting for hours, was stood up.

106
00:08:59,950 --> 00:09:01,710
Yes, I understand.

107
00:09:01,710 --> 00:09:06,460
She's returning the day after tomorrow, and heading right to a lodging place in Yangyang.

108
00:09:06,460 --> 00:09:08,910
This is really too much!

109
00:09:08,910 --> 00:09:10,950
Don't wait for the manager to call back and continue to check.

110
00:09:10,950 --> 00:09:13,690
We don't know what will happen again.

111
00:09:16,390 --> 00:09:17,780
Yes, this is Oh Ha Na.

112
00:09:17,780 --> 00:09:20,440
Hey, girl. You living well?

113
00:09:23,820 --> 00:09:26,320
One week since I came to Seoul.

114
00:09:26,320 --> 00:09:29,580
I completely adjusted to the time difference!

115
00:09:29,580 --> 00:09:31,580
Kang Na Yeong!

116
00:09:34,040 --> 00:09:35,720
How long has it been?

117
00:09:35,720 --> 00:09:37,640
Four years? Five years?

118
00:09:37,640 --> 00:09:39,440
You haven't changed at all.

119
00:09:39,440 --> 00:09:41,160
I think you've changed a bit.

120
00:09:41,160 --> 00:09:42,700
Your style has gotten better.

121
00:09:42,700 --> 00:09:44,740
This girl. Is your husband well?

122
00:09:44,740 --> 00:09:48,250
I got divorced. I did well, right?!

123
00:09:48,250 --> 00:09:50,930
What? It hasn't even been long since you married.

124
00:09:50,930 --> 00:09:54,200
Three months is enough to change your decision.

125
00:09:54,200 --> 00:09:55,780
Why did you divorce?

126
00:09:55,780 --> 00:09:59,180
Because I didn't know why I got married.

127
00:10:00,340 --> 00:10:01,000
What?

128
00:10:01,000 --> 00:10:04,500
Don't ask me about the past. Anyway, you still keep in touch with our old friends, right?

129
00:10:04,500 --> 00:10:07,060
Yeah, why them?

130
00:10:08,480 --> 00:10:10,960
I want to start a new life.

131
00:10:10,960 --> 00:10:11,820
What is this?

132
00:10:11,820 --> 00:10:16,360
I plan to become their life planner.

133
00:10:17,000 --> 00:10:19,200
Na Yeong is like a capricious ball.

134
00:10:19,200 --> 00:10:21,760
Just like a capricious ball you don't know the trajectory of,

135
00:10:21,760 --> 00:10:25,240
she's my best friend from high school who was always someone

136
00:10:25,240 --> 00:10:28,280
who surprised me with her unpredictable actions.

137
00:10:37,800 --> 00:10:41,270
- Bye Oh Ha Na!
- Bye! Sleep well.

138
00:10:51,040 --> 00:10:53,340
Hey, Oh Ha Na!

139
00:10:56,370 --> 00:10:58,150
Na Yeong!

140
00:11:00,580 --> 00:11:04,150
- What brought you here?
- Why did you lie to me?

141
00:11:04,150 --> 00:11:05,780
What lie?

142
00:11:06,730 --> 00:11:07,990
What is with you?

143
00:11:07,990 --> 00:11:12,690
You are dating Won! I saw it all just now.

144
00:11:12,690 --> 00:11:16,540
- No, you know it well too!
- I believed your words.

145
00:11:16,540 --> 00:11:20,550
I believed when you said you guys are not dating. And because you said he didn't  take my present,

146
00:11:20,550 --> 00:11:24,410
I accepted it coolly. But now I realized,

147
00:11:24,410 --> 00:11:26,670
you are in between the two of us.

148
00:11:26,670 --> 00:11:28,710
Hey, Kang Na Yeong!

149
00:11:28,710 --> 00:11:31,810
I saw it all in the group blind date earlier as well. You two

150
00:11:31,810 --> 00:11:33,740
planned the pick ahead.

151
00:11:33,740 --> 00:11:36,860
- What do you mean planned?
- Enough with that.

152
00:11:36,860 --> 00:11:39,350
Did you even give the present to Won?

153
00:11:39,350 --> 00:11:44,450
Do you not trust me? Do you think I'd betray you because of Choi Won?

154
00:11:47,310 --> 00:11:49,810
I am more disappointed, really.

155
00:11:49,810 --> 00:11:53,340
- If you are that innocent—
- Right, it is a misunderstanding.

156
00:11:53,340 --> 00:11:55,310
Let the three of us talk together

157
00:11:55,310 --> 00:11:58,070
- to clear things up.
- What?

158
00:12:06,410 --> 00:12:09,470
From this point onward, everything will be recorded.

159
00:12:09,470 --> 00:12:12,990
I hope you have enough shame not to make the heavens cry (to lie).

160
00:12:15,450 --> 00:12:19,370
Is it right that you got my present, Won?

161
00:12:20,410 --> 00:12:24,260
Don't look at Ha Na and talk while looking at my eyes.

162
00:12:24,260 --> 00:12:27,850
I did get it.

163
00:12:27,850 --> 00:12:29,110
Then?

164
00:12:29,110 --> 00:12:31,730
- But that was a bit—
- You took my gift lightly because you two were dating?

165
00:12:31,730 --> 00:12:34,010
- It's not that.
- I will say it.

166
00:12:34,010 --> 00:12:38,570
Won, you could not accept my present because

167
00:12:38,570 --> 00:12:40,110
you are dating Ha Na.

168
00:12:40,110 --> 00:12:44,710
- It's not like that!
- And Ha Na could not refuse my favo.

169
00:12:44,710 --> 00:12:46,950
because we are friends.

170
00:12:46,950 --> 00:12:49,550
That's why you two lied to me, saying that Won refused it, right?

171
00:12:49,550 --> 00:12:51,490
- No, that is a bit absurd—
- Forget it!

172
00:12:51,490 --> 00:12:56,100
But the keen me figured everything out during the group blind date yesterday.

173
00:12:56,100 --> 00:12:59,410
Now, go ahead if you want to refute my words!

174
00:13:01,890 --> 00:13:04,320
Na Yeong, you really misunderstood everything.

175
00:13:04,320 --> 00:13:07,470
We are really just friends and never deceived you.

176
00:13:07,470 --> 00:13:11,010
- If we tried to deceive you—
- Stop it!

177
00:13:12,070 --> 00:13:13,770
I...

178
00:13:15,000 --> 00:13:17,030
like someone else.

179
00:13:21,250 --> 00:13:22,910
Who?

180
00:13:24,710 --> 00:13:26,620
There is someone!

181
00:13:35,780 --> 00:13:42,990
Timing and Subtitles brought to you by The Timeless Lovers @ Viki

182
00:13:55,910 --> 00:13:57,770
Who would it be?

183
00:13:59,970 --> 00:14:01,990
- Jeong Mi?
- Nope.

184
00:14:01,990 --> 00:14:06,060
Chang Soo likes her and they are an official couple.

185
00:14:06,060 --> 00:14:09,960
Could it be the new math student teacher?

186
00:14:09,960 --> 00:14:14,590
Won is not good at mathematics. But you say he likes the math student teacher?

187
00:14:14,590 --> 00:14:17,990
That's why he can't say it!

188
00:14:17,990 --> 00:14:21,910
Uh, omo. I feel bad for him.

189
00:14:21,910 --> 00:14:24,390
If only he was good at math...

190
00:14:25,690 --> 00:14:28,890
I feel sort of bad too.

191
00:14:28,890 --> 00:14:33,220
Poor guy...

192
00:14:33,220 --> 00:14:34,950
Should we order another ramen?

193
00:14:34,950 --> 00:14:37,990
Yeah, I'm down!

194
00:14:37,990 --> 00:14:40,330
Excuse me!

195
00:14:42,730 --> 00:14:47,060
- So you are going to work for an insurance company?
- Yeah.

196
00:14:48,410 --> 00:14:51,250
Right! Since you've made the decision, do it diligently.

197
00:14:51,250 --> 00:14:54,810
I will introduce all the female employees in my company to you.

198
00:14:54,810 --> 00:14:59,250
Forget the female employees, but find rich and able men.

199
00:14:59,250 --> 00:15:01,570
This is my own strategy.

200
00:15:01,570 --> 00:15:03,720
- What?
- Look.

201
00:15:03,720 --> 00:15:08,050
They would have to write down all their personal information and their assets here.

202
00:15:08,050 --> 00:15:13,990
In this process, I can verify the real ones and the fakes.

203
00:15:13,990 --> 00:15:18,350
That's why you are working as an insurance saleswoman? To find your Prince Charming?

204
00:15:18,350 --> 00:15:19,880
Aren't I really smart?

205
00:15:19,880 --> 00:15:25,670
If you use that brain for your self-improvement, you'd have faster results than searching for a man.

206
00:15:25,670 --> 00:15:32,410
Ugh, this exemplary Oh Ha Na. That's why you are still not married. Others are already married once or twice.

207
00:15:35,050 --> 00:15:36,650
Na Yeong?

208
00:15:36,650 --> 00:15:40,270
- That Kang Na Yeong?
- Yeah, the one who used to like you.

209
00:15:40,270 --> 00:15:42,610
She liked me?

210
00:15:42,610 --> 00:15:48,090
You don't remember? We even had a three-way talk at the cathedral.

211
00:15:48,090 --> 00:15:50,910
Ahh... I was dumbfounded then.

212
00:15:50,910 --> 00:15:55,190
Right. If you didn't confess to us there was someone else you liked then,

213
00:15:55,190 --> 00:15:58,490
Na Yeong and I would have ended our friendship.

214
00:15:59,720 --> 00:16:02,750
But who was the girl you liked back then?

215
00:16:02,750 --> 00:16:05,130
I don't know. I don't remember.

216
00:16:05,130 --> 00:16:06,520
You are lying.

217
00:16:06,520 --> 00:16:10,570
You didn't say who it was because it was a one-sided crush, right?

218
00:16:11,950 --> 00:16:16,510
- Hey! Do I look like someone who would  be in a one-sided crush?
- Yeah.

219
00:16:20,730 --> 00:16:27,340
Look, look! Even at this off-work hour, I am getting a phone call from a female hoobae.

220
00:16:28,910 --> 00:16:31,190
Yeah, So Eun.

221
00:16:31,190 --> 00:16:33,140
Right now?

222
00:16:33,140 --> 00:16:36,560
I  am having dinner with my friend now.

223
00:16:36,560 --> 00:16:38,460
Tell her to join us.

224
00:16:38,460 --> 00:16:41,410
Come on! Tell her to come here!

225
00:16:41,410 --> 00:16:45,150
Tell her to come! Tell her to come!

226
00:16:51,390 --> 00:16:55,600
Say hello to my friend, Oh Ha Na. And this is my hoobae, Lee So Eun.

227
00:16:55,600 --> 00:16:58,070
Hi, Unni!

228
00:16:59,750 --> 00:17:03,170
Glad to meet you, So Eun!

229
00:17:03,170 --> 00:17:04,850
Have a seat.

230
00:17:06,110 --> 00:17:08,330
I am hungry.

231
00:17:08,330 --> 00:17:09,970
Order something.

232
00:17:12,430 --> 00:17:14,950
- This one.
- Will it do with just one?

233
00:17:14,950 --> 00:17:17,350
Order more, I am paying for it today.

234
00:17:17,350 --> 00:17:19,810
Really?

235
00:17:19,810 --> 00:17:24,520
Then, this one, this one and this.

236
00:17:24,520 --> 00:17:26,710
Shall we order this one too?

237
00:17:26,710 --> 00:17:29,760
Unni, do you like this one?

238
00:17:29,760 --> 00:17:33,090
- Yeah.
- Then I like it too.

239
00:17:41,470 --> 00:17:42,910
Uh, omo!

240
00:17:42,910 --> 00:17:46,130
Hey! Are you still having problems using chopsticks?

241
00:17:46,130 --> 00:17:47,990
Give it here.

242
00:17:52,190 --> 00:17:55,430
Look at So Eun using her chopsticks. See how well she's doing?

243
00:17:55,430 --> 00:18:01,390
I didn't use it well at first either. I forced myself to practice a lot because my parents cut off my allowance.

244
00:18:01,390 --> 00:18:03,980
Oppa, ahh.

245
00:18:06,380 --> 00:18:09,320
Don't you like scallions?

246
00:18:09,320 --> 00:18:10,890
No, she doesn't eat them.

247
00:18:10,890 --> 00:18:15,100
Ah... There are people who can't eat scallions.

248
00:18:15,100 --> 00:18:19,120
Yeah, she looks like a person who can chew a raw scallion, doesn't she?

249
00:18:19,120 --> 00:18:20,550
- What?
- Don't you remember?

250
00:18:20,550 --> 00:18:26,010
During lunch time back in school, if you saw just a few pieces of scallion in your stew, you'd say, "Won, Won! There are scallions in my stew!"

251
00:18:26,010 --> 00:18:29,430
Hey! When did I ever go, "Won, Won! There are scallions in my stew"?

252
00:18:29,430 --> 00:18:32,410
Did I? You love scallions!

